article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 75, Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 68
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Jordan Glynn scored a career-high 26 points and Stephen F. Austin defeated Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 75-68 Sunday. Jereal Scott added 19 points for the Lumberjacks (18-8, 9-5 Southland), who handed the Islander their eighth straight loss. Terence Jones scored 15 points, Justin Reynolds had 14 and Demond Watt 13 for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (8-21, 3-11), which hasn't won since beating Stephen F. Austin on Jan. 29. The Islanders shot 66.7 percent after halftime but couldn't rally after falling behind 31-22 at intermission and allowing the Lumberjacks shot 68.2 percent in the second half.
